parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rust of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or injuries.

corrosion on the subframe

loud pop sound while driving
vehicle jerking violently
and rusted out holes near the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failure of the clutch system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position

the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
